claim.claim-text:
1. A method of producing a remainder fraction from the extraction of cannabis comprising:
a) freezing a quantity of cannabis to make frozen cannabis;
b) grinding the frozen cannabis at cryogenic temperatures to produce pulverized cannabis;
c) extracting the pulverized cannabis with a quantity of alcohol to produce an initial cannabis extract;
d) performing a first separation which separates the initial cannabis extract into a first separated cannabis extract and a first residue;
e) performing a second separation which separates the first separated cannabis extract into a second separated cannabis extract and a second residue wherein the second residue is the remainder fraction;
f) diluting the second separated cannabis extract with a quantity of alcohol to produce a first diluted initial cannabis extract;
g) adding a quantity of water to the second diluted initial cannabis extract to produce a second diluted initial cannabis extract; and
h) refluxing the second diluted initial cannabis extract at a temperature of about 80° C.-120° C. for a period of about 1-3 hours whereby the second diluted initial cannabis extract is decarboxylated to produce a second decarboxylated cannabis extract.
